  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-16.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+22.7B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but positioned to buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push above 6605. The massive GEX surge event and PIN regime structure creates a tight 15-point range where dealers will actively dampen volatility, with the 6605 level acting as immediate resistance and 6590 as strong support. Key levels to watch are the flip strike at 6628 (regime change) and the critical 6590/6605 gamma walls that will dictate short-term flow direction.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to stay pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers fighting any breakout attempts.",
